column5: My buddies and I tried Nipp in a bungalow last year and it produced poor results.  Although I heard that was the case for most ppl who fished that lake last winter.  We are contemplating fishing another lake so we can have a better chance of catching some "marble eyes".  We are looking to stay the weekend (on or off the ice).  I posted a question a little while ago "Nippissing or Temagami?" and I'm still not sure what to do.  Does anybody have any recommendations?  Thank you in advance.
Please PM me if you don't want to share your recommendations with the world.  Thank you!
Bay of Quinte has great winter walleye fishing.
Does anbody have some specific lake recommendations?
